the first fifteen fibonacci numbers

slots one and two hold the pair and slot three counts
none of them hold their own value for long

1 <<
11 = @0
12 = @1
13 = @0
!! (13 < @(1)) {
    11 >>           print number
    14 = 11 + 12      get next number
    11 = 12          pass number over
    12 = 14          pass new number
    13 = 13 + @1     increment counter
}
